 Indian author and columnist. He was included in Time magazine's list of World's 100 Most Influential
People in 2010. Bhagat graduated in mechanical engineering at IIT Delhi and completed a PGP at IIM Ahmedabad. 



Born: 22 April 1974 (age 47 years), New Delhi

Website  http://www.chetanbhagat.com/books/


Genre Fiction ,Humour ,Narrative ,Romance Novel,Thriller,
Crime Fiction





The Girl In Room 105
http://www.chetanbhagat.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/the-girl-in-room-105.png


The Girl in Room 105 is the eighth novel and the tenth book overall written by the Indian author Chetan Bhagat. 
The book became a bestseller based on prearranged sales alone. It tells about a IIT coaching class tutor who goes
 to wish his ex-girlfriend on her birthday and finds her murdered.

 originally published:2018

 Author: Chetan Bhagat

 Pages: 304

Genre: Mystery, Thriller


One Indian Girl
http://www.chetanbhagat.com/wp-content/uploads/Front.jpg

One Indian Girl is an Indian Book written by the Indian author
 Chetan Bhagat.[1] . The book is about a girl name Radhika Mehta, who is a worker at the Distressed Debt group of Goldman Sachs, 
the investment bank.

Originally published: 1 October 2016
Author: Chetan Bhagat
Pages: 280
Genre: Fiction


Revolution 2020
http://www.chetanbhagat.com/wp-content/uploads/img_book_5.jpg

Revolution 2020: Love, Corruption, Ambition is a 2011 novel by
 Chetan Bhagat. Its story is concerned with a love triangle, 
corruption and a journey of self-discovery.

Originally published: 2011
Author: Chetan Bhagat
Pages: 296
Genre: Fiction, Politics, Romance



Five Point Someone
http://www.chetanbhagat.com/wp-content/uploads/img_book_1.jpg

Five Point Someone: What not to do at IIT is a 2004 novel written 
by Indian author Chetan Bhagat. The book sold more than a 
million copies worldwide. The Hindi movie 3 Idiots and Tamil 
movie Nanban is based on this book.The book was also adapted
 into a play by the theatre company "Evam. 

Originally published: 2004
Author: Chetan Bhagat
Pages: 270
Genre: Fiction, Buddy